snippet.textDisplay:
Oh, my goodness.What a sweetheart. His howl was hilarious.
~~~~
And...related only by a thread, but something which always comes to my mind when I read of animals being forced to work: I really wish that people would stop riding camels when they visit countries that offer them.
There must be very few that train them up with care and safety, and which also defer to the well-being of the animal instead of prioritizing forced/violent compliance and squeezing in as many rides as possible. It's always bothered me. I don't understand how people are still doing this.
